<br>
Some of both.<br>
<br>
In principle, everyone pays homage to all of the gods, all of the time, but in practice, most people would have a &quot;favorite god&quot; (usually the one your parents worshiped), and they would rarely pay homage to any of the other gods except under certain circumstances.  As you say, different times of the year, there would be a festival for a particular god, and then everybody would worship that god for a bit.  The Festival of Demeter, for example, corresponds with harvest-time, if I remember correctly.<br>
<br>
Also, which god you worship might depend on what you were doing.  Sailors usually worshiped Poseidon, but people who were about to go on a sea voyage would also pay homage to Poseidon.  That wasn't considered betraying their &quot;regular&quot; god; it was just how things were done.<br>
<br>
Naturally, some people who more dedicated to a particular god than most.  You wouldn't too often find a priest of Aphrodite worshiping Diana, for example, though that's not to say it never happened.<br>
<br>
It may be worth mentioning that modern-day Hinduism works much the same way. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umaladominus.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maladominus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/23/02 6:25:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1174.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Should Evil RP Guilds focus on killing GOOD deities?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> When the server went live i chose Roddy the enchanter, as opposed to my old warrior, but all the people who played on test who were going to form our nice evil bertoxxulous guild never arrived so i retired my human for grouping reasons... all the necromancers sped ahead of me, and non of the dark elfs would group with a human.. so i was left a solo enchanter and there was no fun in it, so i returned and made a dark elf shadowknight who i totaly enjoy. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
